Q&A Data.Subject: Xycuno Oobabooga
Q&A Data.Question: What are Xycuno Oobabooga custom nodes for?
Q&A Data.Answer: Xycuno Oobabooga provides custom nodes for ComfyUI to send requests to an Oobabooga instance to assist in creating prompt texts.

Q&A Data.Subject: Xycuno Oobabooga
Q&A Data.Question: What is the preferred installation method for Xycuno Oobabooga custom nodes?
Q&A Data.Answer: The preferred installation method is using git submodules for custom nodes.

Q&A Data.Subject: Xycuno Oobabooga
Q&A Data.Question: What is the default host for an Oobabooga API?
Q&A Data.Answer: The default host for an Oobabooga API is `http://127.0.0.1:5000`.

Q&A Data.Subject: Xycuno Oobabooga
Q&A Data.Question: What is the default maximum number of tokens to complete the prompt in the Oobabooga node?
Q&A Data.Answer: The default maximum number of tokens to complete the prompt in the Oobabooga node is `200`.

Q&A Data.Subject: Xycuno Oobabooga
Q&A Data.Question: What is the default prompt in the Oobabooga node?
Q&A Data.Answer: The default prompt in the Oobabooga node is an instruction to describe an image featuring the ComfyUI mascot.

Q&A Data.Subject: Xycuno Oobabooga
Q&A Data.Question: What is the default seed used in the Oobabooga node?
Q&A Data.Answer: The default seed used in the Oobabooga node is `0`.

Q&A Data.Subject: Xycuno Oobabooga
Q&A Data.Question: What is the default temperature setting in the Oobabooga node?
Q&A Data.Answer: The default temperature setting in the Oobabooga node is `1.0`.

Q&A Data.Subject: Xycuno Oobabooga
Q&A Data.Question: What is the default top_p setting in the Oobabooga node?
Q&A Data.Answer: The default top_p setting in the Oobabooga node is `0.9`.

Q&A Data.Subject: Xycuno Oobabooga
Q&A Data.Question: What is the Outputs of the Oobabooga node?
Q&A Data.Answer: The Outputs of the Oobabooga node is the text returned by Oobabooga, not including `prompt`.
